Hiding a wound that's not healing won't make it go away.  The answer isn't just to wrap another bandage around it, the answer is to get help now.
<br>
<br>
<a href="1_0_1.htm">Wound Care Centers<sup>&reg</sup></a> are unique outpatient treatment centers managed by <a href="hp2_0.htm">Curative Health Services</a>.  The centers apply a comprehensive approach to the diagnosis and treatment of chronic non-healing wounds.  Therapeutic treatment plans are tailored to the individual needs of each patient.
<br>
<br>
The Wound Care Center<sup>&reg</sup> programs have been <a href="1_0_5.htm">successful</a> in promoting the healing of wounds that previously resisted healing and in reducing amputations.
<br>
<br>
If you have <a href="1_0_2.htm">questions</a> about a wound that won't heal, ask your physician or call the Wound Care Center<sup>&reg</sup>.
<BR clear=all>
<center>
<img src="./images/hrs.gif">
</center>
<br>
<B><a href="1_0_2.htm">WOUND CARE QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS</a></b>
<br>
Ignoring the problem can lead to serious infection, gangrene or possible amputation.  Patients with chronic wounds often have questions regarding the care of their wound.  Go to the questions and answers page for some additional information.
<br clear=all>
<center>
<img src="./images/hrs.gif">
</center>
<br>
<b><u>WOUND TREATMENTS</u></b>
<br>
The Wound Care Center<sup>&reg</sup> doctors, nurses and technicians will evaluate your wound 
and review your medical history and general health.  You may have special tests to provide 
information about the flow of blood and oxygen to your wound.
<br>
<br>
Once your test results are in, the Wound Care Center<sup>&reg</sup> 
team will develop a treatment plan based on your special needs.  Healing of your wound will be evaluated at each follow-up visit.  Your program will involve regular visits to the Wound Care Center<sup>&reg</sup> to provide treatment, follow progress, and make any changes that may be required.
<br clear=all>
<center>
<img src="./images/hrs.gif">
</center>
<br>
